    "body": "@noeliaSD @John-44 \r\nWhen the user is adding/removing contacts to the chat, the UI is in a modal state given they have to confirm/reject before proceeding. If we didnt have the confirm/reject controls, we could simply dismiss the list of contacts when the user re-focused the chat input - allowing them to send the message - this feels a little more intuitive.\r\n\r\nHowever, if we want to retain the confirm/reject controls, we need to inform the user somehow that they can't proceed until they have selected either confirm or reject. The best way I can see to do that is to put the chat bar into a disabled (but still visible state). The user may want to review their message while they choose the recipient so I think its better to show it in a disabled state than to hide it altogether.\r\n\r\nThose are just my thoughts! It would definitely be worth getting a consensus with others before proceeding to ensure there are no issues with that solution.\r\n\r\nThe only issue with this solution I can see is that the user cannot simultaneously be editing the message and selecting recipients at the same time. However, the user can always go back and change the recipient list at any time during their writing/editing of the message so that may be a non-issue.",
